cs.LG, cs.CV, cs.IR, cs.CL, cs.MM 

The paper deals with machine learning tasks such as cross-modal text-image retrieval, multi-label image classification, and visual memorability ranking, which are typically associated with computer vision (cs.CV) and multimedia (cs.MM) sub-categories. The paper proposes a deep learning architecture to approximate non-differentiable objective functions, which is a common topic in the machine learning sub-category of learning (cs.LG). The paper also mentions the use of metrics such as mean average precision and Spearman correlation, which are commonly used in information retrieval (cs.IR) and natural language processing (cs.CL) sub-categories.
